oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Johnny Cash interview - 1973-09-10
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Recording of an interview with Johnny Cash (performer), recorded September 10, 1973.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: [Unidentified] introduces Johnny Cash -- Cash talks about how nothing can replace the old Opry house -- Cash talks about how great the new Opry house is supposed to be -- Cash talks about wanting to do live television -- Cash talks about not being in a position to speculate who will win the Country Music Awards -- Cash talks about looking forward to hosting the last Grand Ole Opry television show -- Cash talks about who will be joining him on the show, including June Carter and Maybelle Carter -- Cash says the show will be worth seeing
